<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="724" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/7–1645:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 724<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary
                                            of State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting
                                            Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top
                                        secret</hi></seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="italic">Babelsberg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-16">July 16,
                                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p><gloss target="#t_Victory1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi></gloss> 35. Top secret to Acting Secretary of
                                    State.</p>
                                <p>British Delegation informs us Department proposes issuing
                                    statement July 17th that United States will support Italy’s
                                    admission to international organization and has asked British
                                    Government to do likewise. Would prefer that you postpone action
                                    on this as I desire to <pb facs="0818" n="624" xml:id="pg_624"/>
                                    give consideration to some statement regarding Italy into which
                                    would be incorporated if possible reference to this subject and
                                    to which I would like to consider inviting Soviet Government to
                                    join.</p>
                                <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_BJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>